		<td><b>Animated Game Selection</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I am not a programmer, and this is not related to the actual emulation, but rather, is what I think would be a fun idea for selecting ROMs to load with emulators. With most modern monitors having a 16:9 aspect ratio, and the system originally displaying in 4:3, there is a lot of extra space. As a fun way to select games, there could be an animated section of the screen where games can be selected from a shelf, dragged with the mouse cursor, and loaded into the system.<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=1006&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=1006&amp;t=1" alt="animatedgameselectconcept.png" /></a><br />
			<span class="gensmall">animatedgameselectconcept.png [ 31.25 KiB | Viewed 287 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div>

		

